        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15085",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maners",
                        "name": "maners",
                        "displayName": "Dawid Zamirski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Attached is a patch against SVN trunk which enables $value argument to be an array from which it attempts to extract data for the value XHTML attribute. The $value array must contain a key matching $name and, if it does not, blank ('') value is used instead. This patch doesn't change behavior of existing API and it just adds the new functionality. I have used it for a few weeks with one of my projects and it didn't cause any problems.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maners",
                        "name": "maners",
                        "displayName": "Dawid Zamirski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-11T10:45:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-11T10:45:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17563",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've scheduled this for the 1.1.0 release, which will include a number of other view helper changes as well.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-16T10:33:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-16T10:33:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18665",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've just re-read the issue, and I don't agree with the implementation; if you can pass an array containing the element name as a value, you can certainly pass the specific key in the element:\n\n{code}\n$this->formText('first_name', $post['first_name']);\n{code}\n\nIf you're worried that the element name is not in the array, then you should pre-initialize the array, or use a ternary:\n\n{code}\n$this->formText('first_name', ((isset($post['first_name']) ? $post['first_name'] : ''));\n{code}\n\nYes, it's more verbose, but it's also more explicit and doesn't lead to unexpected results.\n\nNow, if you want support for array syntax in the element names, that's another matter.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-01-29T14:06:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-01-29T14:06:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19662",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Array notation works already, and solutions using existing functionality have been provided in comments.",
